executeCommand

public static String executeCommand(String command)
This method will execute "command" in the respective terminal window.

Parameters:
command - The curl command that will get the data from the web server.
Returns:
The output from the command that was executed, or a String starting with "ERROR" if there is an error during the execution of the command. This may not always return a String containing "ERROR" if something went wrong, however; but if you see "ERROR", then there was 100% something wrong.

getData

public static String getData(String rawData,
                             String dataName)
Gets the JSON value of "data" for a given variable, dataName. This method MAY NOT work if "rawData" is processed, hence the reason for the naming of the variable. You may get the right answer, but with the spacing all janky. It is HIGHLY RECOMMENDED that you only use this method with raw data. Example usage: getData(getData(), "vehicle.trip.arrived") will return the data value: '{"tripSummaryUpload":{"foo":1,"bar":2}}'.

Parameters:
rawData - The data through which we should scan. Typically, this is going to be found by the "getData()" method.
dataName - The String of the varable, or information, we are searching for.
Returns:
The raw data that is associated with "dataName".

getRawData

public static String getRawData()
Gets the raw JSON data from the server. This will return an unformatted String that contains all of the server's data.

Returns:
A String containing all of the data downloaded from the server, or a String starting with "ERROR:" that describes any error that occurred while trying to read the data from the server.

getValidVariableNames

public static String[] getValidVariableNames(String rawData)
Returns a String array containing all of the possible variables that the user can call upon.

Parameters:
rawData - The data through which we should scan for variables.
Returns:
An array containing all of the variable names in the data. Any of these can be called into "getData(rawData, varName)" to get the associated data with that variable.

post

public static String post(String varName,
                          String data)
Posts data to the default group/sensor group.

Parameters:
varName - The name of the variable we are modifying. This needs to be one of the variables provided: tripSummaryUpload, vehicleHealthUpload, homeWindowOpen, homeWindowClosed, homeGarageOpen, homeGarageClosed, homeSmokeAlarmOn, homeSmokeAlarmOff, homeSmokeAlarmBatteryLow, homeFireAlarmOn, homeFireAlarmOff, homeWaterSensorAlarmOn, or homeWaterSensorAlarmOff. Do not add extra quotes.
data - The data that will be associated with "varName". This can be any valid JSON, and if it is invalid, this command will not be guaranteed to have predictable behavior.

post

public static String post(String groupID,
                          String sensorID,
                          String varName,
                          String data)
Posts the given data, "data" to "varName", under the group "groupID" and the sensor "sensorID".

Parameters:
groupID - The groupID to which we are posting.
sensorID - The sensorID to which we are posting.
varName - The name of the variable we are modifying. This needs to be one of the variables provided: tripSummaryUpload, vehicleHealthUpload, homeWindowOpen, homeWindowClosed, homeGarageOpen, homeGarageClosed, homeSmokeAlarmOn, homeSmokeAlarmOff, homeSmokeAlarmBatteryLow, homeFireAlarmOn, homeFireAlarmOff, homeWaterSensorAlarmOn, or homeWaterSensorAlarmOff. Do not add extra quotes.
data - The data that will be associated with "varName". This can be any valid JSON, and if it is invalid, this command will not be guaranteed to have predictable behavior.
